item.description:
Use the following snippet
if(&quot;${CMAKE_SIZEOF_VOID_P}&quot; EQUAL &ldquo;8&rdquo;) MESSAGE(&quot;++ 64 bit architecture&quot;) #set(LIBSUFFIX &ldquo;64&rdquo;) set(PKGARCH &ldquo;amd64&rdquo;) # set(RPMPKGARCH &ldquo;x86_64&rdquo;) else() MESSAGE(&quot;++ 32 bit architecture&quot;) # set(LIBSUFFIX &ldquo;&quot;)
set(PKGARCH &ldquo;i386&rdquo;) endif()

This is what you have to do when saving the video:
ani_.save(&lsquo;output.avi&rsquo;, fps=args_[&lsquo;fps&rsquo;], savefig_kwargs = { &lsquo;transparent&rsquo; : True , &lsquo;facecolor&rsquo; : &lsquo;black&rsquo; }
Argument savefig_kwargs is the key parameter. It is applied to savefig which is called every time a frame is saved into video file. Ref: http://matplotlib.org/api/animation_api.html

